{
  "text": "To investigate whether estrogen regulates miRNA expression, the ER+ human breast cancer cell line MCF-7 was treated with 10 nM E2 for 24 hours, and changes in the miRNA expression profile were analyzed by performing qPCR-based TLDA miRNA assays. Table 2 lists the 26 miRNAs that were significantly downregulated and the 28 miRNAs that were significantly upregulated (greater than fivefold changes) by E2 treatment of MCF-7 cells. Among these estrogen-regulated miRNAs, miR-34b has been shown to regulate tumor progression in a variety of cancers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Because E2 markedly decreased miR-34b expression levels (72-fold), miR-34b was chosen for further study.",
